\par }\pard\plain \s52\ql \li0\ri0\sb100\sa100\sbauto1\saauto1\widctlpar\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin0\itap0\pararsid11284567 \fs24\lang1033\langfe1033\cgrid\langnp1033\langfenp1033 {\fs32\insrsid11284567\charrsid11284567 
These words again emphasize that Jesus Christ is of one essence with the Father, and is God. }{\fs28\insrsid11284567 
\par }{\fs32\insrsid11284567\charrsid11284567 He is called "light of light" because he has his total essence from the Father, just as when a light is lit from another light, it receives therefrom the entire substance of light }{
\cs148\f1\insrsid11284567\charrsid12874251 [Met. Peter Moghila, "ORTHODOX CONFESSION OF FAITH OF THE CATHOLIC AND APOSTOLIC EASTERN CHURCH", "Q. 36. What do the words "light of light" mean?", http://esoptron.umd.edu/ugc/ocf1b.html]}{
\fs32\insrsid11284567\charrsid11284567  
\par There are two kinds of light, created, and uncreated. Created light is material, from source such as the sun, stars, flame, etc. 
\par Uncreated light is the light of God, which always was, and therefore existed before light, and all created things. 
\par This uncreated light is referenced in : "The sun shall be no more thy light by day; neither for brightness shall the moon give light unto thee: but the LORD shall be unto thee an everlasting light, and thy God thy glory. }{
\cs148\f1\insrsid11284567\charrsid12874251 \{20\}}{\fs32\insrsid11284567\charrsid11284567  Thy sun shall no more go down; neither shall thy moon withdraw itself: for the LORD shall be thine everlasting light, and the days of thy mourning shall be ended."}
{\cs148\f1\insrsid11284567\charrsid12874251  [Isa 60:19-20]}{\fs32\insrsid11284567\charrsid11284567  
\par The Apostle Paul makes it clear that the "brightness" of the Father and the Son are equal: 
\par }{\cs148\f1\insrsid11284567\charrsid12874251 [Heb 1:1-3]}{\fs32\insrsid11284567\charrsid11284567  God, who at sundry times and in divers manners spake in time past unto the fathers by the prophets, }{\cs148\f1\insrsid11284567\charrsid12874251 \{2\}}{
\fs32\insrsid11284567\charrsid11284567  Hath in these last days spoken unto us by his Son, whom he hath appointed heir of all things, by whom also he made the worlds; }{\cs148\f1\insrsid11284567\charrsid12874251 \{3\}}{
